## Vercel Speed Insights Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js App Router project.

### Changes Made

**1. Installed Package:**
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` (v2.0.0) as a dependency
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with resolved dependencies

**2. Modified Files:**
- **src/app/layout.tsx**: Added SpeedInsights component to the root layout
  - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component at the end of the body tag (after main content)

### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), I:
1. Fetched the latest installation instructions to ensure up-to-date implementation
2. Identified this as a Next.js App Router project (Next.js 15.5.18)
3. Installed the package using npm (the project's package manager)
4. Added the SpeedInsights component to the root layout file following Next.js App Router best practices
5. Placed the component after {children} in the body tag as recommended by the documentation

### Verification

- Build completed successfully with no errors
- All changes follow Next.js App Router conventions
- The SpeedInsights component will automatically track Core Web Vitals when deployed to Vercel

### Next Steps

To complete the setup:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard (navigate to your project → Speed Insights → Enable)
3. After users visit the site, metrics will be available in the Vercel dashboard

### Files Modified
- webapp/package.json
- webapp/package-lock.json  
- webapp/src/app/layout.tsx
